title: North Moore Street - West Broadway - Varick Street
North Moore Street - West Broadway - Varick Street

original_title: Manhattan: West Broadway - North Moore Street
text:
West Broadway, west side, south from North Moore Street, showing across the Sixth Ave. Elevated structure the Western Union Building outline. Note in the foreground, the Franklin Street station at Finn Square. It is at the latter point where Varick Street starts, diverging northward from West Broadway.

May 2, 1938.

P. L. Sperr.

The same Locale, subsequent to "El" demolition.

July 12, 1939

P. L. Sperr

original_title: Manhattan: West Broadway - North Moore Street
text:
West Broadway, west side, north from North Moore to Beach Streets. At the N.W. corner of North Moore Street is a group of 3-story frame structures with brick fronts. These are No's. 1 and 3 North Moore Street and 242 and 244 West Broadway.

The corner building bears two of these identities (No. 1 and 242). The two story feature, centered in View 2, is of brick construction. This bears No. 246 West Broadway and adjoins the 8-story loft building, No. 248-50 (also 2-4-6 Beach Street).

July 12, 1939
View 1, 2

P. L. Sperr
